-- Australia Reaches 285-5 on First Day of Second Cricket Test With India
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-10-09T16:09:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-09/australia-reaches-285-5-on-first-day-of-second-cricket-test-with-india.html
Australia reached 285-5 on the
opening day of the second cricket Test against India in
Bangalore.  Captain Ricky Ponting scored 77 to lead Australia, which
batted first after winning the toss. The visitors were an
unbeaten 95 at lunch, then lost three wickets before tea and two
after.  Shane Watson scored 57 and Marcus North is 43 not out.
Harbhajan Singh claimed two wickets for India, which won by one
wicket four days ago to open the two-Test series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
